==English==
===Etymology===
Named after [[w:John Langdon-Down|John L.H. Langdon-Down]] (1828-1896), an English physical who described it in the late 1800s. The term was first used in 1961.

===Noun===
'''[[Down]] [[syndrome]]'''

#''(medical):'' condition caused by a chromosomal deficiency, whereby the patients bear a certain resemblance to the Mongoloid race, such as a small head and tilted eyelids.

====Alternative spellings====
*[[Down's syndrome|Down’s syndrome]]<!-- this is the spelling i've been reading the past week or so -->

